name: Entropy Rose
description:
During a visit to a favourite forest, I came upon a lone white rose that had been placed within the mossy, fern-wreathed cavity of a decaying stump.

I was overcome with a spark of deep wonder; who could this rose have been from - who was it dedicated to - and for what reason was it placed in this particular place?

It is something that I will never know, yet all of the potential stories behind the gifting of this rose abound within me.

Camera: Nikon D90
Lens: Kaleinar-3B
